  "An approximation of area using a finite number of rectangles": "",
  "The exact area under a curve": "",
  "A formula for the circumference of a circle": "",
  "A Riemann sum approximates the area under a curve by dividing the region into rectangles, computing each rectangle's area, and summing them all.": "",
  "What does 'partition' mean in the context of Riemann sums?": "",
  "Dividing the interval [a, b] into subintervals": "",
  "Removing discontinuities from a function": "",
  "Splitting a function into even and odd parts": "",
  "Finding the antiderivative of a function": "",
  "A partition of [a, b] divides the interval into n subintervals using points a = x_0 < x_1 < ... < x_n = b. Each subinterval provides the base for one rectangle in the Riemann sum.": "",
  "What is the 'definite integral'?": "",
  "The average rate of change of a function": "",
  "The slope of a tangent line": "",
  "The limit of Riemann sums as the number of rectangles approaches infinity": "",
  "The antiderivative of a function": "",
  "The definite integral of f(x) from a to b is defined as the limit of Riemann sums as the number of subintervals n approaches infinity and the width of each subinterval approaches zero.": "",
  "What does 'signed area' mean in integration?": "",
